<subSubSection id="5EEBB56294668ACBD8CCAFC33923D1B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="AE2FA27A83C1BE4292FCD28B0E63479F" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BD906A647EB8839114693BA29E9B8D4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="9DE5577907C76DC4D3F86B2687FD624E" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Bey-Bienko" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella ligulata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligulata">
<emphasis id="A657075BD6AC8AB78E67B740C8F01560" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella ligulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bey-Bienko, 1957) 
<emphasis id="682424682B03EDCD2107263EDC337C5D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">comb. nov.</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B894E2CC9C4A75BCEB8EF6AE6CF009D" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Blattella ligulata (Bey-Bienko, 1957) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690407" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">7</figureCitation>
), originally in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="9097016BC70AE1FE8A2BDF27FD05E2E0" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EE3F573CD45477677B2E01BC85E7386" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="ACF2E78F20489AF0FBB19194D830B82A" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5079A624DDBCFE8D12957D74A61CD29A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by (
<bibRefCitation id="8A59618C9B2BB17610DB43FCAB123671" author="Roth, LM" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="375 - 397" refId="B42" refString="Roth, LM, 1985c. The genus Symploce Hebard. V. Species from mainland Asia (China, India, Iran, Laos, Thailand, South Vietnam, West Malaysia) (Dictyoptera: Blattaria, Blattellidae). Entomologica Scandinavica 16: 375 - 397" title="The genus Symploce Hebard. V. Species from mainland Asia (China, India, Iran, Laos, Thailand, South Vietnam, West Malaysia) (Dictyoptera: Blattaria, Blattellidae)." volume="16" year="1985 c">Roth 1985c</bibRefCitation>
) because of the symmetrical T10. However, both morphological and molecular data analysis support that this species should be in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2CA2D139D055257C653C222D9B2CF866" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C202AE8B04A0CF8CF24D2E9784C5757F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F19BCBF3F9FF050236F2C4A173B6092D" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Bey-Bienko" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella ligulata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligulata">
<emphasis id="9D3334B5FBAC9F7AAD13C53CDA1CAC03" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella ligulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bey-Bienko, 1957) 
<emphasis id="FC1D26FCA0461BC70126F35BFF965FCE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">comb. nov.</emphasis>
shares some characteristics with 
<taxonomicName id="9A2E1B89FC97BB5FAA8640B9C261B05A" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F15AAC53FE11DA5721FDEAF1768B9486" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: male T10 tongue-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE0AA1806985D7E313535C3F14F7C192" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Blattella ligulata (Bey-Bienko, 1957) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690407" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">7J</figureCitation>
) and T7 specialized with a pair of large pouch-like depressions with a setal tuft between them (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FD755BED2CC0E6EB84706888214142D5" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Blattella ligulata (Bey-Bienko, 1957) comb. nov., male: A dorsal view; B ventral view; C head, ventral view; D pronotum; E maxillary palp; F front femur, ventral view; G seventh abdominal tergite; H tegmen; I wing; J supra-anal plate, ventral view; K left phallomere L median phallomere; M right phallomere; N subgenital plate, dorsal view. Scale bars: 10 mm (A, B), 1 mm (C, D), 2 mm (H, I), 0.5 mm (E-G, J-N)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690407" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">7G</figureCitation>
). In our phylogenetic analysis, 
<taxonomicName id="B9DDDD4A1558F6F13B3B878B6B705633" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Bey-Bienko" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella ligulata" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligulata">
<emphasis id="903F68D4F51C3D46537AEF304560029F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella ligulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bey-Bienko, 1957) forms the basal clade of 
<taxonomicName id="5D183E1307E00E2ADF30229A995BFE9E" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0ACE0A5A0CDCAF61F213937407EA0DD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being the sister of all other 
<taxonomicName id="0FCA244B4813F883BEED4CC0F067DDD3" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9EED62D694F11DEDEC4D31BCD09CAD1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
samples (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DE2F1AF52203C97F83688BA98E3FBFCA" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Maximum likelihood (ML) tree based on three mitochondrial genes 12 S rRNA, 16 S rRNA, COII and two nuclear genes 28 S rRNA, histone H 3. The topologies yielded by Bayesian inference (BI) are almost identical with ML tree (see supplementary material Fig. S 1). Branch labels provide bootstrap support (bs) of nodes in ML and posterior probability (pp) (%) of nodes in BI; (*) indicates the branch label of the corresponding analysis is 100 or 1.0, respectively; (-) means the node is absent for the given analysis." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.80.e62469.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690401" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">1</figureCitation>
, supplementary material Fig. S1).
</paragraph>
